# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# pgp_model.R
# Random Forest model for P-glycoprotein (P-gp/ABCB1) substrate prediction.
#
# Trained from 882 experimental compounds from Metrabase
# (Journal of Cheminformatics, 2015, 7:21).
#
# The model uses 9 physicochemical descriptors calculated by CDK:
# MW, LogP (ALogP), TPSA, HBD, HBA, RB, HeavyAtoms, AromAtoms, MR
#
# Model: Random Forest, 100 trees, max depth = 10
# 5-fold CV: accuracy = 0.6939, MCC = 0.3825
#
# Feature importances:
#   MR          : 0.1833
#   MW          : 0.1588
#   LogP        : 0.1294
#   TPSA        : 0.1236
#   HeavyAtoms  : 0.1149
#   AromAtoms   : 0.0933
#   RB          : 0.0812
#   HBA         : 0.0624
#   HBD         : 0.0530
#
# This model replaces the previous heuristic based on Seelig (1998) and
# Didziapetris (2003), which had 55% accuracy and 35% sensitivity.
# The Random Forest achieves 69% accuracy and 70% sensitivity.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

